 \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Blake\"}, {\"begin\": 530, \"end\": 542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 639, \"end\": 652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.996384715559284, \"rank\": 0.0014637446930805963, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 688, \"end\": 693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999953161, \"rank\": 4.7001297758768115e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles is the big favourite coming into the event after qualifying for the final by a healthy margin, and the drama may centre on the race for silver featuring a Tokyo rematch between defending champion Sunisa Lee of the U.S. and Brazil\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Rebeca Andrade.\", \"from\": 696, \"to\": 951, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 857, \"end\": 862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999998804014, \"rank\": 1.189775497310581e-10, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 898, \"end\": 908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sunisa Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 936, \"end\": 950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebeca Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee held off Andrade for gold in the Tokyo all-around final, from which Biles withdrew due to a potentially dangerous mental block known as the \\\"twisties\\\".\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 1108, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 953, \"end\": 956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999008651, \"rank\": 9.824667700665069e-11, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 966, \"end\": 973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.566493849846779e-16, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}, {\"begin\": 990, \"end\": 995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999998804014, \"rank\": 1.189775497310581e-10, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Andrade\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s all-around score of 57.700 from Sunday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s qualification in Paris is the highest total posted by any woman this year aside from Biles, safely ahead of Lee\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s qualifying score of 56.132.\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1182, \"end\": 1187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999953161, \"rank\": 4.7001297758768115e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Lee is capable of a balance beam routine 0.7 points higher than her qualifying effort, putting pressure on Andrade to repeat her strong preliminary showing.\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1314, \"end\": 1317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999008651, \"rank\": 9.824667700665069e-11, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 1421, \"end\": 1428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.566493849846779e-16, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another set of talented gymnasts are nipping at the favourites\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 heels.\", \"from\": 1472, \"to\": 1544, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breakout 17-year-old Algerian star Kaylia Nemour, known for her daredevil combinations on the asymmetric bars, qualified for the all-around final in fourth with a 55.966 and reigning European all-around champion Manila Esposito of Italy, also 17, was just behind on 55.898.\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1567, \"end\": 1575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9990031024897298, \"rank\": 0.0005929792593004183, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1758, \"end\": 1764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\", \"score\": 0.9997378017034781, \"rank\": 0.00025500109307857526, \"text\": \"Manila\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\"}, {\"begin\": 1765, \"end\": 1773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Esposito\", \"score\": 0.9999920073438443, \"rank\": 7.990250304832411e-06, \"text\": \"Esposito\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Esposito\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phil_Esposito\"}, {\"begin\": 1777, \"end\": 1782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999927760683833, \"rank\": 6.765641950907622e-06, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Qiu Qiyuan, who qualified in seventh with a disappointing total of 54.998, could also threaten.\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1930, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She suffered a fall and other missteps on the balance beam, where she has world-class difficulty, earning her a score almost two points below her likely target.\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 2091, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the men's side, China and Japan will face off once again in Wednesday\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s all-around final after a thrilling team result, where Japan staged a late comeback to stun China.\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2112, \"end\": 2117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.996368144304425, \"rank\": 0.0021016839238525696, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], 