n Daiki Hashimoto of Japan qualified in third with 85.064, though his programme was riddled with uncharacteristic mistakes, and is a contender to repeat as all-around victor.\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2418, \"end\": 2433, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daiki Hashimoto\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\"}, {\"begin\": 2437, \"end\": 2442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.7038288165052581, \"rank\": 0.4205756519638899, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_baseball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A skilled pair of Britons, Jake Jarman and Joe Fraser, who qualified in fifth and sixth, could nudge their way in amid any major errors by the top gymnasts.\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2610, \"end\": 2617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9383761215332105, \"rank\": 0.06564532376730356, \"text\": \"Britons\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2619, \"end\": 2623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Paul\", \"score\": 0.6678726953541858, \"rank\": 0.4972763267590322, \"text\": \"Jake\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Paul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Paul\"}, {\"begin\": 2635, \"end\": 2638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_DiMaggio\", \"score\": 0.9870534076354766, \"rank\": 0.013116285385193705, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbp